and our language is very much

00:05:15.460 --> 00:05:20.300
in the core of the national
identity of Finland and Finns.

00:05:20.300 --> 00:05:23.650
There is a twist there,
which is that we are --

00:05:23.650 --> 00:05:25.720
we have two official languages.

00:05:25.720 --> 00:05:29.920
So it's not only the Finnish
language that is in the core

00:05:29.920 --> 00:05:31.870
of the national identity.

00:05:31.870 --> 00:05:35.540
It is also very much
the Swedish language,

00:05:35.540 --> 00:05:38.710
and the fact that we
are a Nordic country.

00:05:38.710 --> 00:05:42.070
That is a big part of our identity.

00:05:42.070 --> 00:05:51.590
Finnish language is beautiful,
difficult, very expressive,

00:05:51.590 --> 00:06:00.180 position:56%
and I think really quite an exciting
environment to study, to live in.

00:06:00.180 --> 00:06:04.840
And the way -- I mean, the
Finnish language is a little bit

00:06:04.840 --> 00:06:06.150
like Finland.

00:06:06.150 --> 00:06:13.100
It's almost like an island, which
means you have an environment

00:06:13.100 --> 00:06:17.830
where you tend to develop
something quite special,

00:06:17.830 --> 00:06:20.980
and quite different
from anything else.

00:06:20.980 --> 00:06:24.980
And I think the Finnish language
has allowed that kind of a --

00:06:24.980 --> 00:06:30.630
you know, a world of its own
for Finns and Finnish speakers.

00:06:30.630 --> 00:06:39.540
And I think it also shows in the
way the language has evolved.

00:06:39.540 --> 00:06:45.640
Teaching the language, and studying
the language is very important.

00:06:45.640 --> 00:06:50.910
It is like, you know,
history or anything else.

00:06:50.910 --> 00:06:53.550
Like, if you walk the
streets of Washington,

00:06:53.550 --> 00:06:58.370
D.C. and you don't know anything
about the history of the buildings,

00:06:58.370 --> 00:07:02.810
or what has happened
here, it's only maybe 5%

00:07:02.810 --> 00:07:05.390
that you understand
about what you see.

00:07:05.390 --> 00:07:08.190
And that is a little bit
the same with the language.

00:07:08.190 --> 00:07:14.400
If you just hear it, or read it,
and take it, well, maybe it's more

00:07:14.400 --> 00:07:25.100 position:56%
than 5%, but you really get a deeper
understanding, and you can master --

00:07:25.100 --> 00:07:29.790
