Sorry. I'm just going to
turn this on, if it'll work.

01:27:41.810 --> 01:27:43.550
If not, I'll just keep talking.

01:27:43.550 --> 01:27:46.160
So anyway, John Komeinen
in 1937 notes

01:27:46.160 --> 01:27:49.440
that these very factors are
affecting language shift among the

01:27:49.440 --> 01:27:52.170
children of immigrants, though
some token nods to continued use

01:27:52.170 --> 01:27:53.470
of Finnish, mostly

01:27:53.470 --> 01:27:56.320
through Finnish-American social
organizations, were made.

01:27:56.320 --> 01:27:59.150
The pressures of Americanization
were compounded

01:27:59.150 --> 01:28:04.050
by local inter-ethnic social
